claim.claim-text:
17. A device, comprising:
a neural stimulator lead;
a neural stimulator configured to deliver a neural stimulation therapy through the neural stimulator lead;
an antenna lead including at least one electrode for use to remotely detect cardiac activity, the neural stimulation therapy not delivered through the antenna lead; and
a controller configured to remotely detect cardiac activity using the antenna lead, and control the neural stimulator using the detected cardiac activity; and
an implantable housing, wherein the neural stimulator and the controller are in the implantable housing.

20. A method for operating an implanted neural stimulation device having a neural stimulator lead and an antenna lead including an electrode, comprising:
implementing a neural stimulation therapy stored in the implanted neural stimulation device including delivering the neural stimulation therapy through the neural stimulator lead and not through the antenna lead, wherein the neural stimulation therapy includes a programmed duty cycle, and the programmed duty cycle includes a stimulation ON portion followed by a stimulation OFF portion;
remotely detecting cardiac activity using the antenna lead with the electrode to detect heart rate information during at least one of the stimulation ON portion or during the stimulation OFF portion;
controlling the neural stimulation therapy using the detected heart rate information;
using an accelerometer to sense heart sounds; and
using both the heart sounds and the remotely detected cardiac activity to control the neural stimulation therapy performed by the neural stimulation device.
